The paper articulates reflections from two specific researches. Consumption is reference to an epistemological overview on mediatic processes, supported by multi-methodological investigations. It is perceived like a mediated system, implicating on both material and productive process, and also concerning to an affectionate regime, with aesthetic dynamics linked to symbolic dimensions. Consumptions practices are investigated, focusing the body and the processes of youngsterâ€™s urbane subjectivities.